In [[geometry]], the '''quarter hypercubic honeycomb''' (or '''quarter n-cubic honeycomb''') is a dimensional infinite series of [[Honeycomb (geometry)|honeycomb]]s, based on the [[hypercube honeycomb]]. It is given a [[Schläfli symbol]] q{4,3...3,4} or Coxeter symbol q&delta;<sub>4</sub> representing the regular form with three quarters of the vertices removed and containing the symmetry of [[Coxeter diagram#Infinite Coxeter groups|Coxeter group]] <math>{\tilde{D}}_{n-1}</math> for n ≥ 5, with <math>{\tilde{D}}_4</math> = <math>{\tilde{A}}_4</math> and for quarter n-cubic honeycombs <math>{\tilde{D}}_5</math> = <math>{\tilde{B}}_5</math>.<ref>Coxeter, Regular and semi-regular honeycoms, 1988, p.318-319</ref>

