[[File:HC R1-1stellation.png|250px|thumb|right|A partial honeycomb of stellated rhombic dodecahedral cells.|alt=]]

The '''stellated rhombic dodecahedral honeycomb''' is a space-filling [[tessellation]] (or [[honeycomb (geometry)|honeycomb]]) in [[Euclidean 3-space]] made up of copies of [[First stellation of rhombic dodecahedron|stellated rhombic dodecahedron]] [[cell (geometry)|cells]]. Six stellated rhombic dodecahedra meet at each vertex. This honeycomb is [[Isohedral figure#Related terms|cell-transitive]], [[edge-transitive]] and [[vertex-transitive]].

