In [[geometry]], the '''infinite-order square tiling''' is a [[List of regular polytopes#Hyperbolic tilings|regular]] tiling of the [[Hyperbolic geometry|hyperbolic plane]]. It has [[Schläfli symbol]] of {4,∞}. All vertices are ''ideal'', located at "infinity", seen on the boundary of the [[Poincaré hyperbolic disk]] projection.

== Uniform colorings==
There is a half symmetry form, {{CDD|node_1|split1-44|branch|labelinfin}}, seen with alternating colors:
:[[File:H2 tiling 44i-4.png|200px]]
== Symmetry==
This tiling represents the mirror lines of [[iiii symmetry|*∞∞∞∞ symmetry]]. The dual to this tiling defines the fundamental domains of (*2<sup>∞</sup>) [[orbifold notation|orbifold]] symmetry.
: [[File:H2chess 24ic.png|200px]]

== Related polyhedra and tiling ==

This tiling is topologically related as a part of sequence of regular polyhedra and tilings with vertex figure (4<sup>n</sup>).
