In [[geometry]], the '''octagonal tiling''' is a [[regular hyperbolic tiling|regular tiling]] of the [[Hyperbolic geometry|hyperbolic plane]]. It is represented by [[Schläfli symbol]] of ''{8,3}'', having three regular [[octagon]]s around each vertex. It also has a construction as a truncated order-8 square tiling, t{4,8}.

== Uniform colorings ==
Like the [[Hexagonal_tiling#Uniform_colorings|hexagonal tiling]] of the Euclidean plane, there are 3 uniform colorings of this hyperbolic tiling. The dual tiling V8.8.8 represents the [[fundamental domain]]s of [(4,4,4)] symmetry.
